<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="966" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d966">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.00/1725.</note>
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-18"><hi rend="italic">November 18,
                                    1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>I respectfully request instructions as to article 3 of agreement 1,
                            signed October 27, 1910, by Estrada and others, whether you wish me to
                            point out again the pledges therein. The present (second) National
                            Constituent Assembly will adjourn in a few days and has not called a
                            presidential election under the constitution.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gunther.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>